Five people have been killed when a double-cab bakkie collided with a truck on the R521 Dendron Road in Limpopo on Saturday.According to police, the accident took place at around 07: 00 am and a case of culpable homicide will be investigated.Police spokesperson Moatshe Ngoepe said the bakkie caught fire on impact and passengers were burned beyond recognition. Bakkie occupants were burned beyond recognition, but the truck driver sustained minor injuries. DNA tests will be carried out to confirm the identities of the deceased, said Ngoepe.The police further said that the cause of the accident is still not established at the moment.All motorist are advised to avoid using the R521 Dendron Road, but they should instead use alternative routes.-TNA Reporter